Mathematical Functions / Fixed-Point Operations

FractCubeRoot

You can use the FractCubeRoot function to calculate the cube root of a fract number.

fract FractCubeRoot (fract source);
source
The fract number for which the cube root is required.
function result
The cube root of the fract number. This number is a signed value.
DESCRIPTION
The FractCubeRoot function returns the cube root of a fract number.
